label.value: Emulsion for Infusion in Administration System Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an emulsion for infusion presented in an administration system.

label.value: Emulsion for Injection/Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for administration by injection or infusion.

label.value: Emulsion for Injection/Infusion in Pre-filled Syringe Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an emulsion for injection/infusion presented in a pre-filled syringe.

label.value: Emulsion for Suspension for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for use in the preparation of a suspension for injection.

label.value: Endocervical

value.value: Relating to the cervix uteri as the intended site of administration.

label.value: Endocervical Gel Dosage Form

value.value: Semi-solid preparation consisting of a gel intended for endocervical use by means of a suitable applicator.

label.value: Endosinusial Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended to be administered to the sinuses to obtain a local effect.

label.value: Endosinusial Suspension Wash Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a suspension intended for cleaning the sinuses.

label.value: Endotracheopulmonary Instillation, Powder and Solvent for Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and aqueous solvent intended for the preparation of an endotracheopulmonary instillation solution by dissolving the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Endotracheopulmonary Instillation, Powder and Solvent for Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Powder and aqueous solvent intended for the preparation of an endotracheopulmonary instillation suspension by dispersing the powder in the solvent.

label.value: LC Dunn and S Gluecksohn-Waelsh, A Einstein, Carries Sd (Danforth's Short Tail)
Endotracheopulmonary Instillation, Powder for Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dissolved in the specified liquid to obtain an endotracheopulmonary instillation solution.

label.value: Endotracheopulmonary Instillation, Powder for Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dispersed in the specified liquid to obtain an endotracheopulmonary instillation suspension.

label.value: Endotracheopulmonary Instillation, Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of an aqueous solution intended for instillation to the trachea and/or bronchi.

label.value: Endotracheopulmonary Instillation, Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of an aqueous suspension intended for instillation to the trachea and/or bronchi. Preparations for inhalation use are excluded.

label.value: Environmental

value.value: Relating to the surroundings in which the target of the pharmaceutical product is found, as the intended site of administration, e.g. an enclosed volume of water or air; usually the product disperses in the area and is subsequently taken up by the subject.

label.value: Epilesional Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution intended to be administered onto a lesion.

label.value: Epilesional Route of Administration

value.value: Administration of a medicinal product onto a lesion.

label.value: Extracorporeal

value.value: Relating to a body substance or tissue as the intended site of administration, after being removed from the body in order to be treated with the pharmaceutical product and then subsequently returned to the body.

label.value: Emulsion Eye Drops Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for ocular use. Multidose preparations are presented in containers that allow successive drops to be administered.

label.value: Eye Drops, Emulsion in Single-dose Container Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an eye drops emulsion presented in a single-dose container.

label.value: Intoplicine

value.value: A benzopyridoindole derivative with antineoplastic property. Intoplicine inhibits activities of both topoisomerase I and II via intercalating DNA helix, thereby hindering the movements of enzymes along DNA molecules during DNA transcription and replication, respectively. Furthermore, this agent stabilizes DNA-enzyme complexes during unwinding processes by both topoisomerases, leading to double- and single-stranded DNA breaks. Consequently, these effects bring about cell growth inhibition and apoptosis of tumor cells.

label.value: SD Mouse
Eye Drops, Powder and Solvent for Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of eye drops, solution, by dissolving the powder in the solvent.

label.value: Eye Drops, Powder and Solvent for Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of eye drops, suspension, by dispersing the powder in the solvent.

value.value: Solid sterile preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dissolved in the specified liquid to obtain an eye drops solution.

label.value: Eye Drops, Powder for Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dispersed in the specified liquid to obtain an eye drops suspension.

label.value: Eye Drops, Prolonged Release Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile single-dose or multidose preparation intended for ocular use. The active substance is released over an extended period of time.

label.value: Eye Drops, Prolonged-Release Solution in Single-dose Container Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a prolonged-release eye drops solution presented in a single-dose container.

label.value: Eye Drops, Solution in Single-dose Container Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an eye drops solution presented in a single-dose container.

label.value: Eye Drops Solvent for Reconstitution Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a sterile solvent containing no active substances, intended for reconstitution of a usually freeze-dried powder for eye drops.

label.value: Ophthalmic Suspension Drops Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of an aqueous or oily suspension intended for ocular use. Multidose preparations are presented in containers that allow successive drops to be administered. The containers contain usually at most 10 mL of the preparation.

label.value: Eye Drops, Suspension in Single-dose Container Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an eye drops suspension presented in a single-dose container.

label.value: Hygiene Inst, Zurich
Eye Gel in Single-dose Container Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an eye gel presented in a single-dose container.

label.value: Eye Lotion Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of an aqueous solution intended for washing or bathing the eye.

label.value: Eye Lotion Solvent for Reconstitution Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a sterile solvent containing no active substances, intended for reconstitution of a usually freeze-dried powder for eye lotion.

label.value: Eye Ointment in Single-dose Container Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an eye ointment presented in a single-dose container.

label.value: Film-Coated Tablet plus Pessary Dosage Form

value.value: Combination package consisting of a film-coated tablet and a pessary.

label.value: Film-Coated Tablet plus Tablet Dosage Form

value.value: Combination package consisting of a film-coated tablet and a tablet.

label.value: Film-Coated Tablet and Gastro-Resistant Granules in Sachet Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a film-coated tablet and gastro-resistant granules presented together in a sachet and intended to be swallowed together as a single dose.

label.value: Fixed Cryogenic Vessel

value.value: A static thermally insulated container designed to maintain the contents in the liquid state.

label.value: Foot-stab Route of Administration

value.value: Administration of a veterinary medicinal product into the foot of birds.

label.value: Gargle, Powder for Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dissolved in water to obtain a gargle.

label.value: LIS Mouse
Gargle, Tablet for Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of a tablet intended to be dissolved in water to obtain a gargle.

label.value: Gargle/Mouthwash Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for use as a gargle or a mouthwash.

label.value: Gargle/Nasal Wash Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for use as a gargle or a nasal wash.

label.value: Gargling Method of Administration

value.value: The technique of administration of a pharmaceutical product by rinsing the throat and/or mouth with it, holding it in the throat and keeping it in motion by releasing a stream of air from the lungs; after gargling, the product is usually intended to be spat out.

label.value: Gas and Solvent for dispersion for Injection/Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile gas and sterile solvent, either in the same compartment or in different compartments, intended for the preparation of a dispersion for injection/infusion by dispersing the gas in the solvent.
